data.title: Athletes Born on December 9
data.meta_description: Famous birthdays in sport for the 9th of December. Browse birthdays of sports stars, managers and coaches that were born on December 9.
data.text:
Charles "Old Hoss" Radbourn, American HOF pitcher, 1880-91 (won MLB record 60 games & Triple Crown 1884; no-hitter 1883; Providence Grays, Boston Beaneaters, and 3 other teams), born in Rochester, New York (d. 1897)

Willoughby Hamilton, Irish tennis player (Wimbledon 1890), born in Monasterevin, Kildare (d. 1943)

Joe Kelley, American Baseball HOF left fielder (NL stolen base leader 1896 Baltimore Orioles) and manager (Cincinnati Reds, Boston Doves), born in Cambridge, Massachusetts (d. 1943)

Hannes Kolehmainen, Finnish long-distance runner (Olympic gold 1912), born in Kuopio, Finland (d. 1966)

Jim Turnesa, American golfer (PGA C'ship 1952; Ryder Cup 1953), born in New York City (d. 1971)

Colin McCool, Australian cricket all-rounder (14 Tests, 1 x 100, HS 104no, 36 wickets, BB 5/41; NSW, Queensland, Somerset CCC), born in Sydney, Australia (d. 1986)

André Milhoux, Belgian racing driver, born in Bressoux, Belgium

Milt Campbell, American decathlete (Olympic gold 1956), born in Plainfield, New Jersey (d. 2012)

1933 Orville Moody, American golfer (US Open 1969), born in Chickasha Oklahoma (d. 2008)

Deacon Jones, American Pro Football Hall of Fame defensive end (8 × Pro Bowl; 5 × First-team All-Pro; LA Rams, SD Chargers), born in Eatonville, Florida (d. 2013)

Billy Bremner, Scottish footballer (Leeds United), born in Stirling, Scotland (d. 1997)

1942 Dick Butkus, American College-Pro Football HOF linebacker (Uni of Illinois; NFL Defensive Player of the Year 1969, 70; 5×First-team All-Pro; 8xPro Bowl; Chicago Bears), sportscaster (CBS, ESPN) and actor (My Two Dads), born in Chicago, Illinois (d. 2023) [1]

Steve Owens, American College Football Hall of Fame running back (Heisman Trophy 1969, U of Oklahoma; Pro Bowl, All Pro 1971, Detroit Lions), born in Gore, Oklahoma

Tom Kite

American golfer (US Open 1992; 19 PGA Tour titles, The Tradition 2000), born in McKinney, Texas

Dragan Pantelić, Serbian soccer goalkeeper (19 caps Yugoslavia; Radnički Niš, Bordeaux), born in Loznica, Serbia (d. 2021)

World B. Free [Lloyd Bernard Free], American NBA guard (Philadelphia 76ers; Cleveland Cavaliers; Golden State Warriors), born in Atlanta, Georgia

Janusz Kupcewicz, Polish soccer midfielder (20 caps; KS Arka Gdynia, ASSE Saint-Étienne), born in Gdańsk, Poland (d. 2022)

Juan Samuel, Dominican-American baseball infielder (NY Yankees, Blue Jays), manager and coach, born in San Pedro de Macorís, Dominican Republic

Barry Wilburn, American NFL full safety (Philadelphia Eagles), born in Memphis, Tennessee

1963 Dave Hilton, Jr., Canadian boxer, born in Port Credit, Ontario

Josie Cichockyj, British wheelchair athlete (wheelchair racing [WR 5,000m], basketball, tennis, table tennis), born in Huddersfield, England (d. 2014)

1964 Petr Briza, hockey goalie (Team Czech Rep), born in Prague, Czechoslovakia

Joe Ausanio, American baseball player

Dana Murzyn, NHL defenseman (Vancouver Canucks), born in Calgary, Alberta

Caryn Kadavy, American figure skater, born in Erie, Pennsylvania,

1967 Jason Dozzell, English footballer

1967 Ray Agnew, American NFL nose tackle, 1990-2000 (New England Patriots; New York Giants; St. Louis Rams), and executive (Los Angeles Rams; Detroit Lions), born in Winston-Salem, North Carolina

Bill Johnson, NFL defensive linebacker (Pittsburgh Steelers)

Kurt Angle

American 220 lbs freestyle wrestler (Olympic gold 1996), born in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania

Bixente Lizarazu, French footballer, born in Saint-Jean-de-Luz, France

1969 Ramon Garcia, Venezuelan pitcher (Milwaukee Brewers), born in Guanare, Venezuela

Marlin Cannon, American 200m/400m runner, born in Dallas, Texas

Chris Boniol, NFL kicker (Dallas Cowboys, Philadelphia Eagles), born in Alexandria, Louisiana

1971 Clifton Abraham, American NFL cornerback (Carolina Panthers, Tampa Bay Bucs), born in Dallas, Texas

1971 Petr Nedved, Czech NHL center (Team Czech, Pitts Penguins), born in Liberec, Czechia

Fabrice Santoro, Tahitian tennis star, born in Tahiti, French Polynesia

Tony Batista, Dominican baseball infielder (Oakland A's), born in Puerto Plata, Dominican Republic

Wendy Dillinger, American female soccer player and coach, born in St. Charles County, Missouri

Chris Booker, American baseball player, born in West Virginia

Shayne Graham, American football player, born in Radford, Virginia

Stephen McPhail, Irish footballer, born in City of Westminster, London

Ryder Hesjedal, Canadian cyclist, born in Victoria, Canada

Mardy Fish, American tennis player, born in Edina, Minnesota

Nathalie De Vos, Belgian athlete, born in Ghent, Belgium

1982 Tamilla Abassova, Russian cyclist, born in Moscow, Russia

Dariusz Dudka, Polish footballer, born in Kostrzyn, Poland

1983 Jermaine Beckford, Jamaican soccer striker (6 caps; Leeds United, Everton, Leicester City), born in London, England

Wyndham Clark, American golfer (US Open 2023), born in Denver, Colorado

McKayla Maroney

American artistic gymnast (Olympic gold and silver medals 2012) famous for her "not impressed" expression that became a meme, born in Aliso Viejo, California
